Package: FinancialFunctions
Title: Excel-Compatible Financial Functions Powered by Rust
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Tor", "Storli", email = "your.email@example.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides 55 Excel-compatible financial functions implemented
    in Rust via extendr for high-performance calculations directly in R.
    Functions cover annuity calculations, cash flow analysis (NPV, IRR,
    XIRR), asset depreciation, bond pricing, coupon date arithmetic, and
    miscellaneous financial utilities. All functions match Excel output
    exactly and return NA on invalid input rather than throwing errors.
    Batch variants are included for processing large datasets efficiently
    with a single Rust call.
